HEADWORD: Sans
<hw>Sans</hw> <pr>(s⟦aum⟧n; E. s⟦acr⟧nz)</pr>, <pos>prep.</pos>
<ety>[F., from L. <ets>sine</ets> without.]</ety> <def>Without; deprived
or destitute of. Rarely used as an English word.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Sans</xex> fail.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Sans</qex> teeth, <qex>sans</qex> eyes, <qex>sans</qex>
